<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-11T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-11T03:00:00-05:00" n="886" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d886">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">751.67/248: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Istanbul</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-11T10:00:00+02:00">April 11, 1939—10
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 11—8:16 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>14. Department’s 23, April 7, 6 p.m. Conversations with French
                                colleagues, the Turkish Minister for Foreign Affairs and his
                                collaborators, indicate that annexation of the Hatay by Turkey was
                                some time ago agreed to in principle by France, the exact date
                                remaining to be settled. The French are endeavoring to avoid the
                                appearance of unseemly haste in acceding to Turkish demands and the
                                Turks appear willing to cooperate within reason in this respect.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>